elow_Threat() can only increase the set of states where need_upward_RA is true, but only to the extent Non_Crossing_Biased_Climb() can be true when Own_Below_Threat() is false.\"\\n      ],\\n      \"control_flow_impact\": [\\n        \"Affects which branch of the if/else ladder sets alt_sep (UNRESOLVED/UPWARD_RA/DOWNWARD_RA).\"\\n      ],\\n      \"reaches_output\": true,\\n      \"output_variables_affected\": [\\n        \"alt_sep printed to stdout\"\\n      ]\\n    },\\n    \"D2\": {\\n      \"propagation\": [\\n        \"Changes return value of Non_Crossing_Biased_Climb, which feeds need_upward_RA (in both S and M, though combined with D1 differently).\",\\n        \"In M, the added AND conditions can turn a previously-true Non_Crossing_Biased_Climb into false, potentially preventing UPWARD_RA.\",\\n        \"In the upward_preferred branch, the added (Own_Tracked_Alt <= Other_Tracked_Alt) is redundant with the branch’s existing logic: if Own_Below_Threat() is false (i.e., Own_Tracked_Alt >= Other_Tracked_Alt), then S\\'s upward_preferred-branch formula already evaluates to false; thus the extra conjunct does not create new true cases, but can only further restrict (not expand) truth.\"\\n      ],\\n      \"control_flow_impact\": [\\n        \"Indirectly affects RA selection by changing need_upward_RA.\"\\n      ],\\n      \"reaches_output\": true,\\n      \"output_variables_affected\": [\\n        \"alt_sep printed to stdout\"\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  },\\n  \"D_masking_analysis\": {\\n    \"overwrite\": {\\n      \"D1\": \"Not overwritten: need_upward_RA is assigned once and then used to compute alt_sep.\",\\n      \"D2\": \"Not overwritten: Non_Crossing_Biased_Climb\\'s return is used directly in need_upward_RA; no later assignment restores S behavior.\"\\n    },\\n    \"control_flow\": {\\n      \"common_gating\": \"Both programs only compute RAs when enabled && ((tcas_equipped && intent_not_known) || !tcas_equipped) is true; otherwise both return UNRESOLVED. Di